    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "a garden?? that sounds so optimistic, but it doesn't feel like that. it doesn't feel like a cycle or a season. it just feels... final. like the well didn't just run dry, it actually collapsed. i've spent my whole life pouring myself into this, and now there's just nothing left to give. what's the point of just existing if there's no more light to put on the canvas? it just feels like i'm waiting for a clock to run out.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
